ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Active status
Notes: 0=Inactive-Data collected after the 14 month treatment phase/after early termination from treatment phase/prior to treatment phase; 1=Active-Data collected during the 14 month treatment phase while subject received originally assigned treatment regardless of degree of compliance; 2=Active-This is the last active assessment for subjects who were about to violate treatment arm by receiving alternate treatment; 3=Active-This is the last active assessment for subjects who were about to leave the study by moving away; 4=Yes, Active; 5=No, Not Active; -1=Not applicable

ElementDescription: Site
Subject type
Notes: 1=MTA randomized trial subject; 2=Local normative comparison group (LNCG) subject; -1= Not applicable

Parent Behaviors: Mom Busy/Child Sit  Factor 1
Notes: Sum of BLPB1M and BLPB2M minus BLPB5M, none allowed to be missing

ElementDescription: Parent Behaviors: Mom Busy/Child Sit  Factor 2
Notes: Sum of BLPB3M and BLPB4M allowing one to be missing

ElementDescription: Parent Behaviors: School Work  Factor 1
Notes: Sum of BLPB1S and BLPB2S minus BLPB5S, none allowed to be missing

ElementDescription: Parent Behaviors: School Work  Factor 2
Notes: Sum of BLPB3S and BLPB4S allowing one to be missing

ElementDescription: Parent Behaviors: Clean Up  Factor 1
Notes: BLPB2C minus BLPB5C, none allowed to be missing

ElementDescription: Parent Behaviors: Clean Up  Factor 2
Notes: Sum of BLPB3C and BLPB4C allowing one to be missing

ElementDescription: Child Behaviors: Mom Busy/Child Sit  Factor
Notes: Sum of BLCB1M and BLCB2M minus the sum of BLCB3M and BLCB4M, allowing three missing

ElementDescription: Child Behaviors: School Work  Factor
Notes: Sum of BLCB1S and BLCB2S minus the sum of BLCB3S and BLCB4S, allowing three missing

ElementDescription: Child Behaviors: Clean Up  Factor
Notes: Sum of BLCB1C and BLCB2C minus the sum of BLCB3C and BLCB4C, allowing three missing

ElementDescription: Parent Autonomy Control
Notes: Sum of MBLMBF1, MBLSWF1, and MBLCUF1, allowing one missing

ElementDescription: Parent Positive
Notes: Sum of MBLMBF2, MBLSWF2, and MBLCUF2, allowing one missing

ElementDescription: Child Negative
Notes: Sum of CBLMBF, CBLSWF, and CBLCUF, allowing one missing
